                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">758.6114AI/87: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-21T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 21—3:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1100. In the absence of reply to my 1062, July 14, 3 p.m., I have assumed that
                    Department does not desire me to sit on Aaland Islands Commission and have
                    declined to do so. Swedish and Finnish representatives are pressing League to
                    appoint commission without delay. I still think unofficial American
                    participation would be helpful to cause of League with American public.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
